name: head

params.name: source
params.description: DataFrames will show *count* rows of that DataFrame. A list, tuple or other iterable, will show the first *count* rows. Dictionaries will show *count* keys from the dictionary, which will be randomly selected unless you are using an OrderedDict. Strings will show the first *count* characters.

params.name: count
params.description: The number of elements to show from the source.

doc: Displays a specified number of elements in a source object of many different possible types.
